ğŸ§  Why Do We Need Redux?

In large apps:

* Many components need shared state
* Prop drilling becomes messy
* Context API becomes complex

Redux solves this by:
âœ” Centralizing state
âœ” Making state predictable
âœ” Managing complex apps

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· What is Redux?

Redux is a **state management library** used to manage global state in React apps.

ğŸ“Œ Works with React
ğŸ“Œ Follows predictable data flow
ğŸ“Œ Uses single store

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”„ Redux Data Flow (Very Important â­)

Redux follows **Unidirectional Data Flow**:

```
Component â†’ Action â†’ Reducer â†’ Store â†’ Component
```

1ï¸âƒ£ User triggers action
2ï¸âƒ£ Action sent to reducer
3ï¸âƒ£ Reducer updates store
4ï¸âƒ£ Store updates UI

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§© Core Concepts of Redux

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1ï¸âƒ£ Store

Store holds the **entire application state**.

```js
const store = createStore(reducer);
```

ğŸ“Œ Single source of truth

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2ï¸âƒ£ Action

An action is a **plain JavaScript object**.

```js
{
  type: "INCREMENT"
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Must have `type`

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3ï¸âƒ£ Reducer

Reducer decides **how state changes**.

```js
function counterReducer(state = { count: 0 }, action) {
  switch (action.type) {
    case "INCREMENT":
      return { count: state.count + 1 };
    default:
      return state;
  }
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Pure function
ğŸ“Œ No direct state mutation

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Setting Up Redux in React

Step 1: Install Redux Toolkit (Recommended â­)

```bash
npm install @reduxjs/toolkit react-redux
```

ğŸ“Œ Redux Toolkit simplifies Redux

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Create Slice (Modern Redux Way)

```js
import { createSlice } from "@reduxjs/toolkit";

const counterSlice = createSlice({
  name: "counter",
  initialState: { value: 0 },
  reducers: {
    increment: (state) => {
      state.value += 1;
    },
    decrement: (state) => {
      state.value -= 1;
    }
  }
});

export const { increment, decrement } = counterSlice.actions;
export default counterSlice.reducer;
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Configure Store

```js
import { configureStore } from "@reduxjs/toolkit";
import counterReducer from "./counterSlice";

export const store = configureStore({
  reducer: {
    counter: counterReducer
  }
});
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Provide Store to App

```jsx
import { Provider } from "react-redux";
import { store } from "./store";

<Provider store={store}>
  <App />
</Provider>
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Using Redux in Component

```jsx
import { useSelector, useDispatch } from "react-redux";
import { increment } from "./counterSlice";

function Counter() {
  const count = useSelector((state) => state.counter.value);
  const dispatch = useDispatch();

  return (
    <button onClick={() => dispatch(increment())}>
      {count}
    </button>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ `useSelector` â†’ Get state
ğŸ“Œ `useDispatch` â†’ Send action

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ†š Redux vs Context API

| Context API         | Redux                    |
| ------------------- | ------------------------ |
| Built-in            | External library         |
| Small-medium apps   | Large apps               |
| Less boilerplate    | More structured          |
| Simple global state | Complex state management |

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  When to Use Redux?

âœ” Large apps
âœ” Complex state logic
âœ” Many shared states
âœ” Debugging with DevTools
âœ” Team-based projects

